    "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
    "body": "You can use either:\n\n``` js\n{\n  templates: '<a href=\"{{url}}\" class=\"...\" data-facet-value=\"{{name}}\"><span>{{name}}</span>...'\n}\n```\n\nThen\n\n``` css\n.list-group-item[data-facet-value=\"facet value\"] {\n\n}\n```\n\nSo that you do not even have to do a mapping between facet names and \"safe css\" class/id.\n\nWould that work?\n\nOtherwise, you can use `transformData: function () {}` which allows you to modify the data passed to the template and you could generate your css safe name here.\n",
    "created_at": "2015-10-29T08:40:00Z",
