    "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
    "body": "The better reference I have is [CSSWizardry](http://csswizardry.com/2011/09/writing-efficient-css-selectors/) based on [Steve Souders](http://stevesouders.com/efws/css-selectors/csscreate.php). This is from 2011 but I don't think the inner engine of CSS parsing changed that much since. We still parse rules from right to left, so the key selector (the rightmost) should be as specific as possible.\n\nAlso note that if the value you add to the `data` attribute contains `\"` you might have to escape it. `transformData` is safer.\n",
